LASPO prohibition.answer:
Paragraph 5.1 of the SRA Code of Conduct for Solicitors sets out the obligations where a solicitor has a referral or financial arrangement with a third party. The solicitor must ensure:
(a) clients are informed of any financial or other interest the referrer has in referring the client to the solicitor;
(b) clients are informed of any payments the solicitor makes to the referrer;
(c) the arrangement does not undermine the solicitor's ability to give independent advice;
(d) clients referred have not been acquired by means that would breach SRA regulatory arrangements (e.g. by unsolicited approaches / cold-calling);
(e) the solicitor does not enter into arrangements that cause the referrer to breach LASPO or the SRA's regulatory requirements.

The disclosure obligation arises at the outset of the retainer — it is normally included in the client care letter or terms of business.
